# Testing Standards

## Coverage

- 100% line coverage required on new/modified code (filtered output from `just test`).
- Build tag `sqlite_fts5` required for all test/build commands.
- Verify: `cd src && go test -tags "sqlite_fts5" -coverprofile=coverage.out -count=1 ./... && go tool cover -func=coverage.out | grep <fn>`

## Coverage filtering (`scripts/test.sh`)

- **File exclusion**: only `fuzzy`, `mcp_service`, `search_store`, `store`, `embedding` included. `*_init.go` excluded.
- **`// nocov` auto-detection**: uncovered blocks containing `// nocov` stripped from filtered profile. Covered blocks unaffected.
- CLI handlers, OAuth, event handlers, daemon code excluded entirely.

## Test structure

- Table-driven tests for multi-case functions.
- Each `foo.go` → `foo_test.go` in same package. Shared helpers in `testutil_test.go`.
- Name: `TestFunctionName_scenario` with `t.Run` sub-tests.
- Test both success and error paths.

## Mocking & isolation

- DB: in-memory SQLite (`file::memory:?cache=shared`), seed via `newTestStore(t)`.
- HTTP: `net/http/httptest.NewServer` with handler stubs.
- WhatsApp: interface test doubles, never real APIs.
- Files: `t.TempDir()`.

## E2E MCP tests

- Call `MCPServer` tool handlers directly, assert on JSON results.
- Cover every MCP tool with success + error case.
